summary_text: 1. I had just started my first job at a local bookstore. 2. My grandpa was bedridden at home with my sister caring for him. 3. I heard a voice urging me to light a candle for my grandpa's recovery. 4. I decided to walk to the local church despite my hesitations. 5. I prayed sincerely for my grandpa's healing at the church altar. 6. After returning to work, I felt an urge to go home. 7. I found my grandpa miraculously out of bed and talking. 8. My grandpa began his recovery and regained his strength. 9. This experience changed my perspective on faith and prayer. 10. Years later, my grandpa lived a full life before passing away.

1. I was twenty-two and just started my first job at a local bookstore. 2. My grandpa was bedridden and my sister cared for him at home. 3. I heard a voice telling me to light a candle for grandpa's health. 4. I hesitated, but remembered my grandma's words on prayer and faith. 5. I went to the church and lit a candle, praying for grandpa's recovery. 6. After the prayer, I felt a strong urge to go back home. 7. I found my grandpa surprisingly sitting up and talking to my sister. 8. My sister said grandpa felt a surge of energy and could walk. 9. The day marked the start of grandpa's recovery and renewed strength. 10. I often think back to that day and its impact on my faith. 11. My grandpa lived many more years, and we cherished our time together.
